# UI Style Guide

## Component Library Location

All UI components are in `/client/src/shared/components/ui/`
Import using: `import { ComponentName } from 'components/ui'`

## Core Design System

### Color Palette

```typescript
// Primary Colors (defined in tailwind.config.js)
primary: '#000000'      // Black - text
secondary: '#1E4999'    // Dark blue - main brand; links, interactive
tertiary: '#FF6B6B'     // Red - errors, warnings
accent: '#01A29D'       // Green - success, CTAs

// Usage in Tailwind
text-primary, bg-secondary, border-accent, etc.
// With opacity: text-primary-500, bg-secondary-200
```

### Typography

```typescript
// Font Families
font-lora          // Serif - story content, narrative text
font-montserrat    // Sans-serif - UI elements, controls

// Font Sizes (Tailwind defaults)
text-xs, text-sm, text-base, text-lg, text-xl, text-2xl

// Font Weights
font-normal (400), font-medium (500), font-semibold (600), font-bold (700)
```

### Spacing Scale

```typescript
// Based on 4px unit (Tailwind default)
p-1 (4px), p-2 (8px), p-3 (12px), p-4 (16px), p-6 (24px), p-8 (32px)
// Same for margins: m-1, m-2, etc.
```

## Component Patterns

### ColoredBox (Base Component)

```typescript
// Foundation for cards and buttons
<ColoredBox
  as="div" // or "button"
  isActive={true} // Hover effects enabled
  leftBorder={true} // Show accent border
  colorType="secondary" // primary|secondary|tertiary|accent|grey
  className="" // Additional styles
>
  Content
</ColoredBox>
```

### PrimaryButton

```typescript
// Main action button
<PrimaryButton
  variant="primary" // primary|secondary|outline
  size="md" // sm|md|lg
  isLoading={false}
  fullWidth={false}
  leftIcon={<Icon />}
  rightIcon={<Icon />}
  textAlign="center" // left|center|right
>
  Button Text
</PrimaryButton>
```

### Modal

```typescript
// Overlay dialogs
<Modal
  isOpen={isOpen}
  onClose={handleClose}
  title="Modal Title"
  width="md" // sm|md|lg|xl|2xl|5xl|full
  showCloseButton={true}
  closeOnBackdropClick={true}
  headerImageSrc="/path/to/image" // Optional
>
  Modal content
</Modal>
```

### Form Controls

```typescript
// Input fields
<Input
  label="Field Label"
  value={value}
  onChange={onChange}
  error="Error message"
  placeholder="Enter text..."
/>

// Text areas
<TextArea
  label="Description"
  value={value}
  onChange={onChange}
  rows={4}
/>

// Dropdowns
<Select
  label="Choose Option"
  value={value}
  onChange={onChange}
  options={[
    { value: '1', label: 'Option 1' },
    { value: '2', label: 'Option 2' }
  ]}
/>
```

### Icons

```typescript
// All icons centralized in Icons.tsx
import { Icons } from 'components/ui'

<Icons.Close className="w-6 h-6" />
<Icons.ArrowLeft className="w-5 h-5" />
<Icons.ChevronRight className="w-4 h-4" />

// Adding new icons:
// 1. Add to /client/src/shared/components/ui/Icons.tsx
// 2. Export from Icons object
// 3. Use consistent naming: PascalCase
```

### Loading States

```typescript
<LoadingSpinner
  size="small" // small|medium|large
  message="Loading..." // Optional message
  messageSize="small" // small|medium|large
/>
```

### Tooltips

```typescript
<Tooltip
  content="Helpful information"
  position="top" // top|bottom|left|right
>
  <button>Hover me</button>
</Tooltip>
```

## Responsive Design

### Breakpoints

```css
/* Mobile First Approach */
default    /* < 640px */
sm:        /* >= 640px */
md:        /* >= 768px */
lg:        /* >= 1024px */
xl:        /* >= 1280px */
2xl:       /* >= 1536px */
```

## Animation Classes

### Built-in Animations

```css
animate-fadeIn       /* 0.3s fade in */
animate-pulse        /* 2s pulsing */
animate-pulse-slow   /* 4s slow pulse */
animate-sparkle      /* 4s sparkle effect */
animate-spin         /* Continuous rotation */
```

### Transitions

```typescript
// Standard transition
className = "transition-all duration-300";

// Hover transforms
className = "hover:translate-x-1 hover:shadow-lg";

// Color transitions
className = "transition-colors duration-200";
```

## Best Practices

1. **Always use ColoredBox or ImageCard for card-like components** - Maintains consistency
2. **Use PrimaryButton for all buttons** - Don't create custom button components
3. **Store all icons in Icons.tsx** - Centralized icon management
4. **Use semantic color names** - primary, secondary, accent, not hardcoded colors
5. **Mobile-first responsive design** - Start with mobile, add breakpoints for larger screens
6. **Consistent spacing** - Use Tailwind spacing scale (p-2, m-4, etc.)
7. **Loading states** - Always show LoadingSpinner for async operations
8. **Accessibility** - Include focus states, ARIA labels, keyboard navigation
9. **Typography hierarchy** - Use font-lora for story text, font-montserrat for UI
10. **Component composition** - Build complex components from simple primitives
